        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'What is total cost of ownership for a car?',
        acceptedAnswer: {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          text: 'Total cost of ownership (TCO) is the complete cost of owning and operating a vehicle over a specific period, including the purchase price, financing costs (interest), depreciation, insurance, fuel, maintenance, repairs, registration fees, and taxes. TCO gives a much more accurate picture of what a car truly costs than the sticker price alone. For a typical new car costing $35,000, the five-year TCO can exceed $50,000 when all costs are included.',
        },
