        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'What is the biggest cost of owning a car?',
        acceptedAnswer: {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          text: 'Depreciation is the single largest cost of car ownership, typically accounting for 35 to 45 percent of the total five-year cost. A new car loses roughly 20 percent of its value in the first year and about 60 percent over five years. On a $35,000 vehicle, that is approximately $21,000 in depreciation over five years. Buying a two to three-year-old vehicle lets you avoid the steepest depreciation and significantly reduces your total cost of ownership.',
        },
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'How much does it cost per month to own a car?',
